U||   as his do not lightly die away. We should have written long ago, but we
U||   knew nothing of his friends, and there was on him nothing that any one
U||   could understand. He came in the train from Klausenburg, and the guard
U||   was told by the station-master there that he rushed into the station
U||   shouting for a ticket for home. Seeing from his violent demeanour that
