U||   flowers, that looked so fair as life, till one by one we wondered if
U||   she were truly dead; she laid in that so fine marble house in that
U||   lonely churchyard, where rest so many of her kin, laid there with the
U||   mother who loved her, and whom she loved; and that sacred bell going
U||   ‘Toll! toll! toll!’ so sad and slow; and those holy men, with the white
U||   garments of the angel, pretending to read books, and yet all the time
U||   their eyes never on the page; and all of us with the bowed head. And
U||   all for what? She is dead; so! Is it not?”
