U||   laugh at in all that. Why, your explanation makes it a harder puzzle
U||   than before. But even if the burial service was comic, what about poor
U||   Art and his trouble? Why, his heart was simply breaking.”
U||   “Just so. Said he not that the transfusion of his blood to her veins
U||   had made her truly his bride?”
U||   “Yes, and it was a sweet and comforting idea for him.”
U||   “Quite so. But there was a difficulty, friend John. If so that, then
U||   what about the others? Ho, ho! Then this so sweet maid is a
U||   polyandrist, and me, with my poor wife dead to me, but alive by
