U||   on:—
U||   “I suppose this upset him, for when we were in town on Thursday last he
U||   had a sort of shock.”
U||   “A shock, and after brain fever so soon! That was not good. What kind
U||   of a shock was it?”
U||   “He thought he saw some one who recalled something terrible, something
U||   which led to his brain fever.” And here the whole thing seemed to
U||   overwhelm me in a rush. The pity for Jonathan, the horror which he
U||   experienced, the whole fearful mystery of his diary, and the fear that
