U||   and stood silent.
U||   “She is one of God’s women, fashioned by His own hand to show us men
U||   and other women that there is a heaven where we can enter, and that its
U||   light can be here on earth. So true, so sweet, so noble, so little an
U||   egoist—and that, let me tell you, is much in this age, so sceptical and
U||   selfish. And you, sir—I have read all the letters to poor Miss Lucy,
U||   and some of them speak of you, so I know you since some days from the
U||   knowing of others; but I have seen your true self since last night. You
U||   will give me your hand, will you not? And let us be friends for all our
U||   lives.”
U||   We shook hands, and he was so earnest and so kind that it made me quite
U||   choky.
U||   “And now,” he said, “may I ask you for some more help? I have a great
U||   task to do, and at the beginning it is to know. You can help me here.
