U||   a desecration; I shall not give my consent to anything you do. I have a
U||   duty to do in protecting her grave from outrage; and, by God, I shall
U||   do it!”
U||   Van Helsing rose up from where he had all the time been seated, and
U||   said, gravely and sternly:—
U||   “My Lord Godalming, I, too, have a duty to do, a duty to others, a duty
