U||   such as in households is used in the coal-cellar for breaking the
U||   lumps. To me, a doctor’s preparations for work of any kind are
U||   stimulating and bracing, but the effect of these things on both Arthur
U||   and Quincey was to cause them a sort of consternation. They both,
U||   however, kept their courage, and remained silent and quiet.
U||   When all was ready, Van Helsing said:—
U||   “Before we do anything, let me tell you this; it is out of the lore and
U||   experience of the ancients and of all those who have studied the powers
U||   of the Un-Dead. When they become such, there comes with the change the
U||   curse of immortality; they cannot die, but must go on age after age
U||   adding new victims and multiplying the evils of the world; for all that
U||   die from the preying of the Un-Dead becomes themselves Un-Dead, and
U||   prey on their kind. And so the circle goes on ever widening, like as
U||   the ripples from a stone thrown in the water. Friend Arthur, if you had
U||   met that kiss which you know of before poor Lucy die; or again, last
U||   night when you open your arms to her, you would in time, when you had
U||   died, have become nosferatu, as they call it in Eastern Europe, and
U||   would all time make more of those Un-Deads that so have fill us with
U||   horror. The career of this so unhappy dear lady is but just begun.
U||   Those children whose blood she suck are not as yet so much the worse;
U||   but if she live on, Un-Dead, more and more they lose their blood and by
U||   her power over them they come to her; and so she draw their blood with
U||   that so wicked mouth. But if she die in truth, then all cease; the tiny
U||   wounds of the throats disappear, and they go back to their plays
U||   unknowing ever of what has been. But of the most blessed of all, when
U||   this now Un-Dead be made to rest as true dead, then the soul of the
U||   poor lady whom we love shall again be free. Instead of working
U||   wickedness by night and growing more debased in the assimilating of it
U||   by day, she shall take her place with the other Angels. So that, my
U||   friend, it will be a blessed hand for her that shall strike the blow
