U||   Only think that we, your true friends, are round you, and that we pray
U||   for you all the time.”
U||   “Go on,” said Arthur hoarsely. “Tell me what I am to do.”
U||   “Take this stake in your left hand, ready to place the point over the
U||   heart, and the hammer in your right. Then when we begin our prayer for
U||   the dead—I shall read him, I have here the book, and the others shall
U||   follow—strike in God’s name, that so all may be well with the dead that
U||   we love and that the Un-Dead pass away.”
