U||   and for centuries after, he was spoken of as the cleverest and the most
U||   cunning, as well as the bravest of the sons of the ‘land beyond the
U||   forest.’ That mighty brain and that iron resolution went with him to
U||   his grave, and are even now arrayed against us. The Draculas were, says
U||   Arminius, a great and noble race, though now and again were scions who
U||   were held by their coevals to have had dealings with the Evil One. They
U||   learned his secrets in the Scholomance, amongst the mountains over Lake
