U||   strait-waistcoat, manacled and leg-ironed, even to a gaol; but let me
U||   go out of this. You don’t know what you do by keeping me here. I am
U||   speaking from the depths of my heart—of my very soul. You don’t know
U||   whom you wrong, or how; and I may not tell. Woe is me! I may not tell.
U||   By all you hold sacred—by all you hold dear—by your love that is
