U||   I thought that the longer this went on the wilder he would get, and so
U||   would bring on a fit; so I took him by the hand and raised him up.
U||   “Come,” I said sternly, “no more of this; we have had quite enough
U||   already. Get to your bed and try to behave more discreetly.”
U||   He suddenly stopped and looked at me intently for several moments.
U||   Then, without a word, he rose and moving over, sat down on the side of
U||   the bed. The collapse had come, as on former occasion, just as I had
U||   expected.
U||   When I was leaving the room, last of our party, he said to me in a
U||   quiet, well-bred voice:—
